                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002"/>
                    <title type="complete" ref="LIT5888AsmatPrayer"/> Against illness.
                    <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual"/> Aleph, written by a secondary hand.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#185v" facs="188"/>
                    Prayers for healing and protection. Written in secondary hands
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#186r" facs="188"> f. 186r, left</locus>
                    Calendar of the Shadows of the Months, Ḥäsäbä Säʿatat, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐሰበ፡ ሰዓታት፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#186r" facs="188"> f. 186r, right</locus>
                    <title type="complete" ref="LIT4624Prayer"/>. Concludes with magical characters.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ምድምያስ፡ ምድምያስ፡ ምድምያስ፡ የሐቂ፡ የሐቂ፡ ያብ[ራ]ሳቂ፡ አድኅኖ፡ ለወልደ፡ [ብ]ራስቂ፡ አድኅኖ፡ እምሕማመ፡ ውግዓት፡ ለገብርከ፡ ልብነ፡ ድንግል።</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <desc>
                      Text has been added in the margins by an untrained hand throughout the manuscript (e.g., <locus target="#159v #160v" facs="162 163"/>).
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001"/>
                    scrawls
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#52v #53r" facs="055"> f. 52v-53r, bottom</locus>
                    scribal exercise of several lines of <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Chp58"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#71v" facs="074"/>
                    The midpoint of the Psalms is marked with the text <foreign xml:lang="gez">መንፈቀ፡ ዳዊት፡</foreign> ʿhalf of the Psalterʾ
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#142r" facs="144"/>
                    a prayer for the owner of the manuscript. The name of the owner has been erased
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#186r" facs="188"/>
                    mentions Ləbnä Dəngəl (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ልብነ፡ ድንግል፡</foreign>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#186v" facs="187"/>
                    pen trials of the syllabary (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ፊዳል፡</foreign> ʿfidalʾ)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
